Add an ITS-G5 / 802.11p regulatory entry (5850-5925 MHz @ 20 MHz, 33 dBm
EIRP) to the DE country regdb so the kernel allows operation on the DSRC
channels enabled by the ath9k 802.11p patch.

Forward-ported from OpenWrt-V2X 21.02.1 (regdb 21.04 -> regdb 2026.03.18).

--- a/db.txt
+++ b/db.txt
@@ -591,6 +591,8 @@ country DE: DFS-ETSI
 	(5470 - 5725 @ 160), (500 mW), DFS, wmmrule=ETSI
 	# short range devices (ETSI EN 300 440-1)
 	(5725 - 5875 @ 80), (25 mW)
+	# ITS / 802.11p (5,9 GHz band, ETSI EN 302 571)
+	(5850 - 5925 @ 20), (33)
 	# WiFi 6E
 	(5945 - 6425 @ 320), (23), NO-OUTDOOR, wmmrule=ETSI
 	# 60 GHz band channels 1-4 (ETSI EN 302 567)
